ANTHRAX - TURKEY (02): (ANKARA) BOVINE
**************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 28 Aug 2018
Source: Ahval News [edited]
https://ahvalnews.com/health/anthrax-outbreak-turkish-farm


A farm near the Turkish capital of Ankara has been placed under quarantine following an outbreak of anthrax, Turkish news website Haberturk said on [Mon 27 Aug 2018]. The alarm was raised after 50 cattle at a farm in Ankara's Gölbaşı district showed symptoms consistent with anthrax infection. The animals were amongst a group of 4000 imported from Brazil in the run up to last week's Eid al-Adha, the Muslim Feast of the Sacrifice. Following an examination of the farm and affected cattle by Gölbaşı's Agriculture and Forestry Directorate, the farm was placed under quarantine.

A statement issued by Turkey's Meat and Dairy Directorate confirmed that test results had returned positive for anthrax and reassured the public that the outbreak had been contained.

"All necessary precautions have been taken to prevent the disease from spreading to other animals outside the farm," the statement said, adding that there was "no worrying situation."

